    "Although this rate is subject to change depending on the text and experiment, our results suggest that we can achieve state-of-the-art, sub-human clinical error rates by carefully engineering and subsequently validating LLMs to produce safe outputs.",
    "Our study is limited in several ways.",
    "Firstly, the sample size of medical transcripts used was relatively small; the sample size was chosen to balance the trade-off of annotation volume required for the comparison of different experiments against sample size and number of experiments performed.",
